Diabetes Data

Graphs

Change Within Calendar Year (CY)

Change in A1c Calculated (Last A1c in CY - First A1c in CY) - Therefore, negative number suggest improvement (i.e.Final A1c=5% - Starting A1c=6% = -1%) during the calendar year

Data frame used is grouped by patients and year of care. Each patient has 5-6 observations. (3440 observations for 652 individuals)

Change Between Encounters

This uses the dataframe that includes all observations for all patients with 5 years of continuous care (8817 observations for 652 patients).

Differences in A1c from the previous A1c were created. A binary variable for diabetes encounter was created to identify if the previous encounter was with a diabetes care navigator or educator. Mixed effects with patient id as random effect.
